{"id": 223751862, "title": "India vs Argentina Live Score, FIH Pro League hockey: Harmanpreet Singh and co eye first win of Antwerp leg", "text": "India vs Argentina FIH Pro League Live Score: Indian men's hockey team take on Argentina on Sunday in their final match of the FIH Pro League mini-tournament in Antwerp. Harmanpreet Singh and co looked like a vastly improved side during their 2-2 draw against the Olympic champions on Saturday. India had lost to Belgium 1-4 in their earlier match on Thursday but bounced back to give a good fight against the hosts. The Indian men's hockey team, however, are yet to win a match in this leg and would like to get that corrected against Argentina, another team that they will face in the group stage at the Paris Olympics. In the previous match against Argentina, India played out another 2-2 draw before clinching a bonus point from the shootout, on a day PR Sreejesh was sensational between the posts. It wasn\u2019t a win on Saturday. But less than 48 hours after a 4-1 drubbing against Belgium, India responded by holding the Olympic champions to a 2-2 draw, before missing out on a bonus point in the penalty shootout. India had two very well-taken field goals, created \u2013 but failed to convert \u2013 penalty corners, at times displayed the same old mistakes but also showcased something different, if not new: intent inside Belgium\u2019s \u2018D\u2019. Read more about that here by Mihir Vasavda. Follow IND vs ARG Live updates below", "summary": "", "url": "https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/hockey/hockey-india-vs-argentina-live-score-fih-pro-league-match-today-harmanpreet-singh-9352397/", "image": "https://images.indianexpress.com/2024/05/Harmanpreet-Singh.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 16:03:03", "author": "Vinayakk Mohanarangan", "authors": ["Vinayakk Mohanarangan"], "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.25}